Source: ubuntu-game-session
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: ubuntu-game-session contributors <ubuntu-game-session@localhost>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
              build-essential
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: ubuntu-game-session
Architecture: all
Depends: gamescope,
        sxhkd,
        gdm3,
        snapd,
        ${misc:Depends}
Description: Ubuntu Game Session (Steam OS-like gaming experience)
 Installs a Gamescope-based Steam Gamepad UI as an optional Wayland session.
 Users can select "Ubuntu Game Session" from the GDM login screen to launch
 the full-screen Steam interface — a Steam OS-like experience on Ubuntu.
 .
 Suitable for desktops and laptops as an optional manually-selected session.
 Install ubuntu-game-handheld for the full handheld console-mode experience
 with automatic boot into gaming mode.

Package: ubuntu-game-handheld
Architecture: all
Depends: ubuntu-game-session,
        hhd,
        acpi-call-dkms,
        ${misc:Depends}
Description: Ubuntu Game Session autologin for handheld gaming PCs
 Configures GDM to automatically log in to Ubuntu Game Session on every boot,
 suitable for handheld gaming PCs (Lenovo Legion Go, Steam Deck, and similar).
 .
 Installs and configures:
  - GDM autologin into Ubuntu Game Session on every boot
  - Handheld Daemon (HHD) for TDP and controller management
  - HHD overlay for in-game quick access
  - Seamless switching between Ubuntu Game Session and Ubuntu desktop
  - Virtual keyboard for touchscreen / handheld input
 .
 Depends on ubuntu-game-session and hhd. Remove the package to fully revert
 to original Ubuntu behaviour.
